<h5 id="head-79d425b0a93a68194134130f37177964883af77c">Deathwatch:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 This level looks filled with evilness. Whee! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I don't remember, do you always enter Deathwatch in the same place? I think so.. Anyway, I'm in a tiny little room. Magic Mapping shows me small adjacent rooms and a path leading towards something that IIRC is a large open area (mapping radius doesn't go that far.) I kill a few assorted snagas and find a fortune cookie. On a whim, I eat it. It says: "Kill, kill, kill, kill, kill, kill!" I take this as a good omen 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Yup, there's that open area. How spoily should I be? Well, we're in the spoilers section. I'm not going to tell you where the artifacts are, though! But this open area, there's a lot of snagas, orcs, uruks etc that are more or less evenly spaced out. I duck back out and continue up a corridor, on the left hand side of the map, kill a a few more critters including a skeleton snaga, then enter the main area. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Like I said, I'm on normal/normal, so my speed is only +5, so my stealth is 'excellent'. I start killing the spaced out critters one by one, and the rest are not (yet, anyway) waking up. There's Lagduf, the Snaga, somewhat in the middle, surrounded by (the remaining) 20 or so orclikes. I progress directly towards Lagduf and kill him. He drops a robe and a lance. A couple of cave orcs have woken and are milling around. The lance is heavy and has slowed me. I destroy it. Really, none of this stuff is anything I can use, so I'm likely to sell all of it, which the possible exceptions of Cammithrin and Maedhros. I polish off all the rest (I'm feeling much better now). Orcs have opened the doors from both the north and the south. I guess I'll go north. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Nothing difficult here - skeleton cave orc and a uruk captain are the worst so far. In the process, I see an interesting message: "You kick the Snaga in the ankle./The Snaga starts limping slower." Do monk attacks actually cause slowing? (It makes sense, if it does.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 So far, no interesting booty. On my way back through the open area, though, I go to the two trunks I left behind before. I fail to disarm both of them and both blow in my face. (I definitely do need to do something about that.) One has only AU. The other yields a Rapier of Extra Attacks (1d6) (+14,+19) (+1 attack). 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I head down from the open area, explore it, then go west of the open area, reading another scroll of magic mapping as I do. Hill orcs, Black orcs, Ogrillons, and yup, there's Grishnakh, the Hill Orc. I take out the shaman first, then Grishnakh (that was easy). 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 In clearing out the area north of Grishnakh, I find a Potion of Wisdom. Yay. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Going south/west (as it were), more of the same orc types. This is really not difficult at all; that dumb room one DL up from here was much, much harder. So I'm feeling rather foolish now at all my elaborate preparations. Still, I seem to remember the last unique being a little harder, and there could have been random unique(s), too. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I round the corner and there's Golfimbul, the Hill Orc, with his buddies. The escort (less the ones I've already killed and those out of sight) is around 25 black orcs, half orcs and ogrillons. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I remember this now. It's a bigger escort. I get confused, and am suddenly down to 176/257, I'm not sure by what. I'm dodging magical attacks again. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I back into a corner - there's a little 2x2 room there with a door - and let them come at me while I chug a CCW. It gorges me (?!?) but I'm back to normal quickly, but still only 190/257. I cuss, shut the door, and chug another before they open it again. This time I don't get gorged. 211/257, fine. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I emerge, kill a bunch of them, get confused, and CCW again. I'm surprised I don't get gorged. There's fewer of them now, and I finally reach Golfimbul. 5 blows kill him. I almost miss that I did kill him because more escort is coming at me. I go straight after the one remaining shaman and kill it. Remaining cleanup is easy. 
</p>
