<h4 id="head-5473108da2f852a44f53a95d1a8451f69f200cb1">CL29</h4>
2 points to barehand, 1 to dodging, 50 left over. Spot check: 
<pre>AC: 105
HP: 264
AU: 111602
Pt: -1785 (sigh)
4 blows/round
8-384 dam/round
brisk-&gt;+8 speed
</pre>According to my spreadsheet, if I've finally got it right, if I'm carrying 96 pounds total load and no armor, my chance to dodge is now (for a L30 monster): Dodge melee attack: 99.23% Dodge bolt attack: 33% Not too shabby! And this is pretty consistent with what I saw: what caused the most damage were missile and spell attacks...and traps. Most monsters couldn't lay a finger on me. In fact, I'm not sure if anyone did... I wasn't watching that closely, but I didn't see it ever happen. <h5 id="head-580a776c6b642fccec58ff95f40d16a839dd873b-3">Observations:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Dodging *ROCKS*. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Deathwatch is a piece of cake, but the bottom of Orc Caves is no joke for a character without rpoison and an area-based attack. The lack of rconf/SI/etc didn't help either, despite my high "AC" and speed. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Getting rpoison is now a major priority. The biggest issue is that I can find all sorts of rings and amulets, but I need ones that have multiple resists/powers...and the problem with those is they are hard to find. And rpoison is going to become rapidly more important. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I've very glad I held onto the ammo for my crossbow. It came in quite useful a few times as a semi-substitute for an area attack. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Did I mention I'm not thrilled with Manwe? I still can't figure out why I had that sudden drop in piety that took me down to -3000ish. Does killing *evil* priests bother him, too? 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Slime molds eaten: 3 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Heaviest thing I'm now carrying is ID scrolls. Still looking for rod bits, but from experience, ID-types are a lot deeper. Staves don't carry enough charges for my needs, unless I carry a bunch of them, and that weighs too much. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I make stupid mistakes, that's obvious. But I bet you do, too 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Still sitting on skill points in wait of FF. I know I'm sadly lacking in a lot of basic skills. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I keep wondering what Music ability would do for this character... but unless someone tries to go out of their way to convert me, I'll probably not go there. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I'm also considering Possession. The few times I've tried it before I always have died messily, and it scares me a bit, but I do have that dragon corpse burning a hole in my pocket. If FF offers it and there's nothing else screamingly better, I'll try it. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Also still contemplating those supplementary magic schools Manwe gives access to. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
The next installment? Some of the following, anyway. 
</p>
