<h5 id="head-33d1982b1d81f0206cd1e064b4b28a761b469678">Lothlorien Spider Quest</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Precog, stare &amp; memorize, duck into trees. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Kill off top part of area, rest for more mana, precog, target, go thru trees; dodge/kill/duck, kill first few areanas, then first elder areana. Then another elder takes me down to about half hp, but I kill it, dodge back into trees and rest. Precog tells me where the others are. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I find a good corner, and line up a number of elder areanas, areanas, and other spiders, and kill maybe 10 of them (including 2-3 elders) in a row. I find myself at 189/266 and dodge fully into the trees to heal up, then kill a bunch more. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 An Areana (or an Elder Areana?) finally starts summoning, and now there's a lot more beasties to dispose of. I try Mindwave and find out that spiders resist that. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I dodge in and out, come face to face with another elder and a few areanas, and get confused. Phase Spiders teleport me to the lower right hand corner of the map and I hurridly dodge into the trees, and rest there until I can see clearly and have my mana back. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The whole key is to come in on a diagonal so there is only LOS on one spider at a time, then dart back out to the trees to rest/heal if needed. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
