<h4 id="head-ea79e73722ac49e26836fd3a95e417577d9868b5">CL32</h4>
I spend a point each on barehand &amp; dodging. Then I blink. Two levels?! I doublecheck. Yes, CL32. Cool. But... I had 7 skill points leftover when I was CL30. I leveled, spent two points, and now I've got twelve, which means I had 15 before?!? Then I remember that I leveled during the spiders quest last night -- I was just too busy to note it down - it was after I stopped typing out the details. <p>
OK, Mayfair asked what my kit was. I was about to post a link, but (doh) with luck I'll be making many more updates to oook, so here we are. This is what I'm about to head to the Old Forest with: 
<pre>Equipment:
Light Crossbow 'Hirth'
Rings of Levitation and Invisibility
Amulet of Resistance
Feanorian Lamp
11 Bolts (hrm, getting low... I *do* use them occasionally)
Shovel
Carrying:
Junkart of remove fear/cure poison
40 CCW
15 Scrolls of Teleportation
5 WOR
50 ID
9 Satisfy Hunger
Wands of Manathrust and Noxious Cloud
Staff of Disarm
25 Empty Bottles
</pre>Now that I've got Mindcraft, I'll probably dispense with those wands eventually. The Manathrust one currently does 11d4 damage. Pulverize can do 12d8. But I don't have all *THAT* much mana yet (only 43) so the wands are backup. 
</p>
<p>
I doublecheck which level that death fate is on... 18, then it's time for the Old Forest, which spans levels 13 to 25, slightly deeper than the Orc Caves. Thunderlord-teleport to- 
</p>
