 I get hit by a spell from a shaman. In the loot, I find a potion of invisibility and quaff it, to stack with my RoI. This ceases all spell action (that I notice, anyway), but increases the 'milling around' factor, too. Much mayhem later, my piety is now -923, first time back up from under -1000. 
