    <li>
<p>
 I'm not quite sure what happens next, but I wind up in a room with a whole bunch of undead and a few uruks, and quickly turn on praying. Crypt creeps are summoning more, too. I back down the corridor to limit the flow, and soon I'm up about 300 Pt to -1588. Yippee. In the same room, there's a handful of MH dragon worms. I kill them, then see something pick up a worm corpse and blink out. Precog shows two poltergeists in the trees. I let them be and check the loot. I've only two ID scrolls left. A pair of boots turns out to be +2 - oh well. Snake egg, staff of recovery, demonblade, cutlass, ring of rfire... yadda. Then, under yet another Amulet of Infravision (I've been finding scads of those!) I find and ID with my last scroll: A Shield of Deflection [10,+16]. I might as well sell that. I'm done with this level and pack is full, so- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-1df3a221d576f88a753eb802683fa2569bac1c8c-12">Lothlorien:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Did I mention I found a Ring of flying under some rubble? The shield sells for ~8600. Vampiric dagger sells for 10k cap (I'm lazy.) Junkart does not sell and *ID*s for...summon pet??? That's the second one of those, and I've never seen that power before this character. Weird. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Out of curiosity, I get a quote on Travak: 793 AU. Heh. I was going to Mathom it, but my house is full, so I sell it. Assorted other sell/clean house/restock. Piety now at -1542. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I try to find a better digger, but the only Picks around are also (+1). Drat. I hate to do it, but I blow an inventory slot on the wand of Thrain. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I sleep at the Inn, but morning shows no new inventory that matters to me. I'm very low in ID scrolls (13) and a tetch low in CCW (34), but I can live with that. WOR - 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-48efa5d779db6ec2231f8dcb9b05326a9881f07f">Old Forest 23 / good:</h5>
I see another quylthulg (or however that's spelled) in the distance, but there's a down stairs only a few steps away, so- <h5 id="head-0c6430478eee5457830c330129ce21c6abadf766">Old Forest 24 / looks like any other level:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Small level - 4 sectors tall, one wide. Air hounds, quickly done with, and a Fountain of Sleep. I move out into a water streamer and run into...hello, 9 Aquatic Hounds, and a Globefish. In the distance there's a Bronze dragon worm. I try to backpedal, get hit by a water bolt and am stunned and confused. This is bad, even though my hp are 219/284. I'm now mobbed by Aquatic Hounds. Next move: 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 'The Aquatic golem wakes up.' The Globefish starts breathing gas. That's enough for me: I'm fine now, but there's way too much opportunity for YASD here. I chug a CCW to rid myself of confusion, and dive into the trees... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 and emerge in a room with a stack of Forest trolls, Flying skulls, etc, which I hadn't precog'd. Piety! *Vroom* 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I finally find another Slime Mold. (Total to date: 4) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 There's a way to line up those Aquatic hounds and kill them one by one - a variant of a corner of the room trick, ducking back into the trees when I have to, to heal. Its that breath that hurts. I take them out, though. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I find a fountain of Heroism and fill just a few bottles. Might help me with Old Man Willow, who's on the next level down. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Take one step, fall over a Water naga (never have seen one of those, either) who drops an un-ID'd potion (restore WIS) and a few other things, and then I'm fighting Hill trolls who are slogging through the shallow water at me. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 There's a room partially sliced off by the water streamer that is half full of Mirkwood Spiders. Piety! *vroom* I head back into the water - there's another fountain out there in the middle - when I find myself surrounded by Sand mites. Darn. I hate these things. The fountain is of Corruption. I get out of the water and head for the stairs. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-3868d8379d9f80460819d05aeead18da45fd3534">Old Forest 25 / excellent:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Big ol' water room plus a bunch of corridors, slightly smaller than usual map. I get away from the water room to start, and check the corridors/rooms. Fountain of Stupidity. I find an un-ID'd rod tip, but I've only got 9 ID scrolls left. I'll wait to see if it pseudos first - its probably frost bolt or something. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Wandering around, I don't look where I'm going and trip... ooof. A Chaos Ball trap. It confuses me, drains life, makes me hallucinate, destroys a weapon in my inventory, and leaves me at 197/284. I stagger into the trees and heal up. My WIS is also drained (I'm not sure when that happened) but I find I'm also carrying a potion of restore wisdom, so I quaff that too. Nothing I can do about the lost 11k XP though The last few times I've been at the temple I'd thought about getting and carrying a few Potions of Restore Life Levels, but I didn't. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Continuing to wander, I look for Old Man Willow. I find and kill a Forest wight, first one I've seen. Then I run smack into Khim, son of Mim. He drops a light crossbow and a tulwar, I'll check them later. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I trip over a giant turtle, and then a green dragon worm. I really should precog more often. I precog, and see a checkerboard pit with a stack of hill trolls and a single hummerhorn. I try to sidestep it, but they all come piling out of the trees after it, including a bunch of hummerhorns. I run for it, and kill a fair percentage of them. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 More dragon worms, then a Red dragon bat. Where's the Old Man? A bit of Precog reveals a Vampiric ixitxachitl but no OMW. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Oops, there he is. I initially mistake him for a vampiric mist, try to run him over, then pause when he doesn't run over promptly. THAT is a record. I think that's the fastest I've ever, ever killed Old Man Willow. Let's see here. 22 blows kills him. I've probably killed him with fewer blows or bolts, but in elapsed time, this was darned fast. He missed me once, and never touched me. He drops.... Metal Brigandine Armor, a Long Bow, and Small Metal Shield. No jewelry, darn it! Armor = Resistance, Bow = Extra Shots, Shield = randart. I wander just a little more and sight-see at the Piranha pools, then WOR- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-1df3a221d576f88a753eb802683fa2569bac1c8c-13">Lothlorien:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Rod tips are Nothing &amp; Door/Stair location. The randart shield isn't fancy: sust WIS and CON, FA, rdark, rconf. Also in my pack is a Dagger of Aman +1 attack, which I save to sell elsewhere, a Tulwar of Slay orc, and a ring of rnexus. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Not quite done restocking yet, but I'll stop here. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-94c91589dd1e585dbf254e12e8d72b1d6dc57c87">Observations/etc:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Old Forest was boring, as I expected, except for those two vaults, though even they were not impressive. I had hoped for a better haul from the bigger one. Also, that digging issue was rather irritating. Must find a better digger. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I now have rpoison (phew) and a temporary source of SI via Precognition. I still need rconf, rblind, and positive Piety would be a nice thing. Another god quest would be nice. And oh, how I would like a source of Reflection! 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<strong>Next?</strong> Not sure, probably Lothlorien Old Mage quest, plus Land of Rhun (think: hydras!), Maze or Sandworm, and I'll probably duck back into Mirkwood as well. I'd love to get the Gondolin house, but not without rconf/rblind or at least until I've got a lot more mana or Magic Device under my belt. Symbiosis would be nice, too, even just a point or two for extra HP. 
</p>
<hr size="3">
 I was planning on finishing the Land of Rhun before posting, but Notepad maxed out on me, and I had to use Wordpad to come to a good stopping place. I could have continued with Wordpad, but I don't want my individual posts to get *too* long. So, I'll post this now, and the rest as soon as I can. <h3 id="head-bdb6020e0aa00595c4d614667b2b7395015e6fd2">A Day in the Life #8: CL32-CL33 (The Land of Rhun DL22-36 - incomplete)</h3>
Recap: Barrow Downs, 1st God Quest, Orc Caves, Lothlorien spider quest, and Old Forest are done. Partway down Mirkwood. Have houses in Bree and Lothlorien; residing in Lothlorien. I need (amongst other things) rconf, rblind, and Piety. I have a temporary source of SI. Rfear would be nice, though. Reflection would be wonderful. <h4 id="head-e66d9b4fa78207480886ef8c34f810d5aa0e5464">CL32, continued</h4>
Spot check: 
<pre>AU 81414
HP 284
SP 43
Pt -1169
5 blows/round, 10-480 damage/round
12 unspent skill points
Slime molds eaten: 4
</pre>Oooh, look, I've one more blow per round since I last looked. Cewl. <p>
<em>Lothlorien:</em> No ID scrolls at all, and I need to clear out the house a bit. Some weapons to go to Gondolin for sale; rings, potions of speed, an Areana skeleton to go to Bree, etc. 
</p>
<p>
I dare the north route from Lothlorien to Gondolin for the first time. (Of course, I've left my shiny new Climbing Set at home, I forgot about it!) But I make it without incident. I've avoided it til now for fear of ambush; in my experience, ice fields seem to be more dangerous that way than other terrains, the same way deep water areas are. (I don't know if this is true.) 
</p>
<p>
<em>Gondolin:</em> 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Here I find my scrolls of ID. I buy the whole stack of 99; I'll stash the leftovers. I also buy out all 31 CCWs in town. The Dagger of Aman sells for 30k, sigh. Nothing good in the BM, and no decent bolts either. I rest for the night. More CCWs, IDs, a few Restore Life Level potions, a bunch of +0,+0 bolts (to be enchanted later and hopefully combined with those I'm carrying now.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I swing by the BM and see something VERY interesting: A Feanorian Lamp of Boldness. I'm currently carrying a plain Feanorian Lamp, and lugging around a junkart of remove fear/cure poison. I just got a ring of poison resistance, so... I peer at it for a while. It costs a little over 50k AU, and I have 97k. I *really* don't want to buy it. I manage to steal it and breathe a huge sigh of relief. The new lamp doesn't give rfear, but a power of remove fear at a cost of 5 mana. I can live with that for now, though I'm not going to ditch the junkart right away, just in case. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The BM has a randart Sheaf Arrow (1d5) (+15,+1: acid, elec and frost damage, slay dragons, orcs, giants, demons, undead, *slay* natural creatures. I'm tempted, but I'm not giving up my crossbow for it! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I belatedly realize I should have taken Mindcraft to 25 at least, and take care of that with 4 skill points. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
Side trip to Bree: Dump stuff, find nothing good, head back to Lothlorien. On the way back down, I find and pop down the stairs to the Land of Rhun, then climb back out. Then I get a new fate, rah. 
</p>
<p>
<em>Lothlorien:</em> 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Fate: I may meet a Jackal on L1. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 All stocked up and nowhere to go. I consider doing the troll glad quest in Bree, but I do NOT want to accidentally run into that Ringwraith yet, so I wait. Hmm... I think I'll do Rhun, as fast as possible, just to get it out of the way. With any luck, I'll find a 5-headed hydra... Rhun covers DL 26-40, with Ulfang on the bottom. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I was going to use the Thunderlord tower, as I'm back up to nearly 100k AU, but why bother - it's not that far, so I go overland. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-d3d2c2136eae2e16f87eb1e003a5b8de2934e5fa">Land of Rhun 26 / excellent:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Precog shows me a Ranger, a Paladin, and stack of Earth hounds. I move north, the panel changes, and I see in the distance....another vault. Good thing I have Thrain with me, huh? 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I outdistance the hounds and get to the vault. It's small to medium size: 40 wide by 15 high. As I'm circling the vault to see what's in there, the Earth hounds catch up with me and I kill them (and a pack of elite uruks) off. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The vault has an outer wall an an inner one, the inner one surrounds many various small rooms interconnected with doors. It has many hounds in it (light, dark and acid), a dark elven lord, clairvoyant, mindcrafter, young MHD, a 3-headed hydra (darn!), a louse, a grave wight, a Qulthulg, and a LOT of other stuff, including breeders and a pack of novice mages. I'm probably going to get blinded a lot if I'm not careful. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I pick a corner where a bunch of dark hounds have come into the outer corridor (the idea being I can pick them off first), cast Precog, and use Thrain to get in. I immediately get blinded, but due to Precog, I can actually still see. How cool is that? 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I can see where the traps are, and try to disarm one, but it goes off. If Slappy hadn't already been an "it", Slappy would be now. I work my way around the corridor to the doorway leading to the interior. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I fight my way inside - acid and dark hounds are at the forefront, along with the mindcrafter &amp; clairvoyant. I'm blind again but I can still see them. And then sometimes I really am blind - and I think my precog has worn off, but then I can see again even though I'm blind. This is weird. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 A pukelman takes a bit of killing, then I'm into the next room, chasing down army ants. Precog has worn off. I get into the next room, which is fairly large and with an open doorway leading directly into the room beyond, and cast Mindwave to good effect - a bunch of things die, most of which I can't see, but at least a few Phase spiders get it. With any luck, I'll get teleported past all the traps right into that next nest. (There's a big, 3-deep barrier of traps I'd just as soon bypass if I can.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I pick up an unID'd potion, kill an army ant and a fire vortex, and sure enough, here I am with the Phase spiders &amp; others, and the Q is in sight, too. Mindwave kills many in the room, but the Q is immune, so I go straight for it. Or try to - I get teleported back along the way I came in by a room or so, but a few more mindwaves take care of that, and then I kill the Q before it can summon. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I'm into then novice mages (mixed in with assorted other creatures), get confused, chug a CCW, and keep going, using Barehand once my mana's down to 5. Soon everything immediately around me is dead and I hide around the door jamb to rest, killing anything that comes around the corner at me. Mana'd back up, I pare my pack down of all the {good} and {average} items, cast Precog, and look to see what's left: that louse (ergh), the young MHD, the hydra, lots of light hounds, and wide assortment of other things like war bears, hardened warriors, rock lizards, etc. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 First up is the hydra, which is easy. Light hounds, then the dragon (takes a number of hits, but it never hits me). I roll over the remaining beasties, I'm frantic now to get at that louse, which is in the most central room, though I've been closing doors behind me just in case. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I get there, kill few few that have multiplied, and I'm done. I start cleaning up loot, and an Inertia Ball trap whaps me HARD for half my hitpoints. Ouch. I don't think I'll try to disarm that one again. I manage to get back out without any serious problems (a trap or two of poison daggers is all.) I'm definitely getting better at disarming. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Loot: A trap set, a ring of extra attacks(-1) (oh well), INT potion, 2 potions of enlightenment, potion of resistance, 2 potions of curing, a wand of Firewall, staves of Fiery Shield and Identify, shield o' RC, and a cap of regeneration. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The potion of INT is nice, it gives me 8 more mana. I keep the other potions; the rest'll get sold. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I keep on going towards the far side of the map (cruising for anything interesting, esp. hydras), and see Ibun, Son of Mim. He drops a good weapon, and I go on. I do find another 3-headed hydra. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-3a26650a8d9a9183ca15628fdbfe462ecfa497e1">Land of Rhun 27 / excellent:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I *was* going to WOR back out, but the level feeling has me curious. I wander the level looking for the explanation. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The answer: Another vault! This one has Sangahyando of Umbar in it, a huge slew of novice mindcrafters, hounds, a handful of young dragons, and other schtuff. Current monster count with precog is 83. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 This vault is wider than the last one, but not so tall. It's also open, and monster are coming out after me, mainly novice mindcrafters and hounds. A LOT of hounds. And many of them are cold hounds and they are breaking my CCWs... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Sangahyando shows up; I trade blows with him, and he blanks my mind 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
I return the favor by offing him. After this, I get wound up in clearing the vault and don't record anything for a while, but nothing terribly interesting happens. I'm running low on ID and CCW. Something drains my experience (might have been a trap, or a wight), and I realize that along the way, the few potions of restore life levels I've been carrying have been destroyed, probably by those darn Cold hounds. 
</p>
<p>
Pot of CHA, shroom of restoring (thank you - int and wis) 
</p>
<h5 id="head-3d5319a86d596331090aefab5b8b56d8ebd02782">Land of Rhun 28 / very good:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I wander the level, killing assorted things, looking for anything interesting, and find....not much, a potion of CHA. My pack's full and I'm out of ID (not helped by that blank of memory). My piety's back to -853, though, yay. I WOR out- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<em>Lothlorien:</em> 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I batch-ID everything. I find an Orc pick (+2) and some bolts of Acid, which I keep, several wands (charm, strike, etc), and staves (firey shield, wings of winds). 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I restock. Wow, I've never tried really using Thrain before, and recharging it is pretty darned cool! There's not enough CCWs in town, though, and no Restore Life Levels, so I swing by Minas Anor. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<em>Minas Anor:</em> Nothing good at the BM. There are Restore Life Levels, but no CCWs. I quaff a RLL, return to CL32, and receive my second God quest, quite some way from my current position and northeast of Lothlorien. Yipee. I might as well go to Gondolin, then, instead of Bree. 
</p>
<p>
<em>Gondolin:</em> 
</p>

