    <li>
<p>
 I decide to find the quest entrance and pick up a few extra scrolls of Sat Hunger. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<em>Overland:</em> I wander, and get another fate. I burn a handful of scrolls of sat hunger and don't find the entrance, so I go on to Bree. I'm at Bree before I realize I've wandered so long the nearer towns have certainly refreshed their inventories already. Oh well. 
</p>
<p>
<em>Bree:</em> I would love to know what Slappy's luck is. She's now got ANOTHER death fate... on DL 1. Again it's night at Bree, and between night and the next morning, I'm up to 45 CCW. Back to Lothlorien. 
</p>
<p>
<em>Lothlorien:</em> Only two more? It'll have to do. Onward... 
</p>
<h5 id="head-5192c7cf6174a438ca07acd631bc9ea6e2121e08">Land of Rhun 28 / strangely lucky:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Intending only to go downstairs, I kill a nether worm mass, cast precog and try to sneak past a cluster of Nexus hounds. Doesn't work, and I get teleported clear across the level. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I land and on the visible monsters list are Beorn and Ulwarth, Son of Ulfang, along with a few hounds and assorted others. I find that last to be rather amusing, since Daddy is guarding L40. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I beat on Ulwarth for a while and eventually kill him. He drops good double chain mail. He doesn't hurt me, but those blasted Cold hounds catch up and start breaking my CCWs. (Fortunately Ulwarth is dead by now, so he isn't healed by them.) I see Beorn through the trees and make for him - he's sleeping - and push past him to let HIM deal with the hounds... then dodge into a room in the trees and let Beorn take my back. He guards me until I find a stair down to- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-b838628b197f356390642dd285c37dc19aae53f2">Land of Rhun 29 / superb:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I land next to a big cluster of flying skulls. I make sure to turn prayer on, then zip through them. Moving along and looking for the cause of the level feeling, I run into 15 firehounds, who succumb to Mindwave very nicely, thank you! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I wander, finding nothing that interesting, and then fall into the middle of a batch of acid hounds. Controlled teleports takes me a ways away and (intentionally) right next to a Bullywug shaman, whom I kill. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
The shaman was right next to a building. I duck inside, close the door on the hounds side, and go out the other. (Yes, I could kill them too, but I would like to keep my potions/etc.) 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 The hounds are still after me. I find a fountain of cure critical insanity and drain it. Precog and looking at the big map ('M') show me the probable cause of the level feeling: A jelly pit. Yecchh. I use major teleport (there's no down staircases anywhere near), kill a dark elven lord, and go down to- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-38e83f42d1034d03068f10628bd2751c91f2372b">Land of Rhun 30 / strangely lucky:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I consider just going down again, but I might as well trawl for uniques and vaults and hydras. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 At first, all I manage to dredge up are hounds and assorteds. I'm soon trailing a tail of energy hounds that are trying to catch up with me when Beorn comes up on my visible list, and I see a baker's dozen of dark eleven warlocks in a clump. They quickly die to Mindwave, leaving a large swath of loot, mainly potions. The energy hounds use up the rest of my mana in Mindwave and I kill the last of them by hand. (I want them dead ASAP so as not to disturb the warlock loot.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The haul from the warlocks is pretty good: Potions (one each) of INT, DEX, CHA, and Enlightenment, a junkart (Green Tome-&gt;Tenser's Alteration Manual), a staff of Fiery Shield, and a 0,0 Mage Staff. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I go find Beorn and wake him up. Slugabout, sleeping while I'm in a fight!!! Beorn *insists* on summoning Fire hounds anytime I run into a monster, which is worse than the monsters themselves. I repeatedly dismiss them and consider dismissing Beorn, too, but I'm a little superstitious aobut that, so I let him tag along. He pays me back a short while later by summoning a pack of multi-hued hounds. Yippee. A bit more wandering (pack is full, must ID/weed it), and I go down to- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-ca2d8b49f56901f22e1064439f873124e983ba63">Land of Rhun 31 / good:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I land, cast Precog, and immediately notice this is a small level. The width of the map fits on my screen. There are dark hounds and elite eruks running around. A bunch of Mindwaves later there is loot to pick through: pebbles of slay undead, dwarven double chain mail, rings of rcold and sustain. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Further along, a room full of novice mindcrafters. I plan to examine this level fairly carefully since there's usually a high density of dungeon trash. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 There's earth hounds, too :/ and lookee there, a big cluster of 21 uruks. Then mountain ogres, more hounds... and a pesky novice paladin I manage to scare but I can't charm it. Then a young green dragon. (And a whole bunch of other critters.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Eventually, I'm done. I've got another potion of resistance, a potion of death (which I lug along thinking to throw at someone, but I should probably use it fast, or destroy it, lest some cold hound blow it up while I'm carrying it ), rod tip of slow monster, a spectral lance, and some wands. I WOR out- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<em>Lothlorien:</em> The junkart sells; it activates for teleport (range 100) every 45 turns. I dither, and buy it back. Restock and WOR- 
