<h5 id="head-6d7f9f6a1f309410609103729f0791e989ccdfa0">Land of Rhun 31 / looks like any other level:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Except that from where I've landed, I can see a little teeny vault. It looks like a Maltese cross inside a box. No, it's not a vault either, it's just a special room. I haven't seen one like this before. Just a couple pieces of junk lying inside, but inspecting them says "you found it lying on the ground..." not "...in a vault on..." 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I wander, then find another special room (a foursquare one) with... ack, vibration hounds, who all come charging after me, and about 20 killer bees, plus a bunch of orcs, etc. I get stunned almost immediately, and teleport away. I wind up near where I started, and go down a level to- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-2cfbf576855982cfd864e32e2bc701e2bf1c0971">Land of Rhun 32 / excellent:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 A smaller level. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I keep finding 3-headed hydras, but no 5-headed... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 More young green dragons (I found a baby MHD last level or so), a bunch of ghouls, a zombie Druid... my Piety's slowwwly been coming up. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Still not finding much. Well, there's an imp, and there's a vampire, first I've seen--that was easy. On the ground: A ring of sound resistance. &lt;BG&gt; Can't really use it right now, but as a swap??? 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 A bit further down, a cluster of 24 Gnome mages, an evil eye and a hardened warrior off in another direction. I go after the gnome mages, who summon a few things (guardian naga, a giant beetle) and I get mostly through them before I realize I'm forgotten to pray again. Blast it all! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 It's always weird finding water creatures in Rhun, somehow, despite there certainly being enough water around to explain it. I've seen a whale in the vis monsters list (didn't bother tracking it down), and I just killed an aquatic golem. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 On the floor: Potions of STR and DEX. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Here we go. Mim, Betrayer of Turin. That's more like it. (There's also a Crypt Thing off in a room; that 'L' gave me a start at first.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I cast Character Armor because I *think* I remember Mim being a spell caster. (I don't bother checking.) Mim mostly gets beaten the heck up by me. I watch and for a long time see nothing but him getting struck and stunned. Then I see two misses by him, a dodge by me, and a little while later, he casts an acid ball at me. (Yup, I remebered correctly.) I'm fine at 277/284, while he's at '**'. Finally I see a message "Mim... flees in terror! Mim... is no longer stunned." I cast Pulverize at him, which dazes him, and he flees again, down to one '*'. He steps away from me, I catch up, and one more blow kills him. THEN I see I forgot to pray again. Rrrrrr... alright, that's it, I'm just leaving it on from now on. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I go after the Crypt Thing. At first I'm doing just fine, then *WHAM* I get mind blasted for nearly half my Sanity (152/245), serious damage, blinding, and then it blinks away... thank goodness i'm carrying a potion of healing and a potion of cure serious insanity which I've found along the way... quaff them, then it blasts me AGAIN, blinded and confused, and down to Sn 110/245. This is not cool. I chug a couple CCWs and teleport away, then rest like crazy until I can see straight. No, wait, I'm still not seeing straight, but there are other beasties around here including hounds...not to mention which, I'll bet that Crypt Thing can teleport. Too much risk. I WOR out- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-1df3a221d576f88a753eb802683fa2569bac1c8c-14">Lothlorien:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Having just said I'd leave praying on, I turn it off before resting until I can really see straight again. A potion of cure insanity and a little trip to restore INT, and I'm feeling much better. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I'm feeling a little sheepish at having run like that. Should I have stuck it out? Maybe so. Then again, even with tactic set on 'coward' (giving an 'excellent' saving throw), that Crypt Thing was hitting me for big ol' chunks of Sanity. I might've ended up a vegetable, instead...and that would result in an extremely dead Slappy! *shrug*. Just to rationalize a bit: My pack was full anyway (And yes, I need more Spirituality...) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Other stuff that turns up in my pack: A Venomous Katana (3d4) (+5,+13), Elven Paper Armour of Resist Cold [4,+9] (+3 to stealth), a staff of Vision, a wand of Teleport Away (keeper!), and an Oil of Wolf. Everything except the wand gets sold. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Time to weed the house again. I load up assorted potions (healing, resistance, etc), the two rods I've found so far. I pick up the junkart of remove fear/cure poison, and pause. I was going to stash it in Bree, but: though I have remove fear via my lamp, I hate blowing CCWs on poison. I'll carry it a while and see how much it gets used. I also finally remember to bring my Climbing Gear, doh! 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-22abd8b59dd7b09205bdf7fd658bd53da9f48d73-8">Bree:</h5>

