    <li>
<p>
 I dump off the potions, start to offload the rods, and voila, the Bree House is now full. Hrmmmm I take the rings of protection and flames and destroy them (they'd been stolen so I can't sell them), sell the oil of mouse and pots of cure light insanity. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I look at the scrolls of teleport in my inventory. I can't read them when I'm blind or confused. My mindcraft teleporting spells will work when I'm blind, but not when I'm confused. But I can't use mindcraft if I'm out of mana. The scrolls stay. (I figured this out with another mindcrafter quite a while ago, but thought I'd repeat the logic here for others.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I'm sorely tempted to toss Thalkettoth, Cammithrim and Maedhros in the Mathom house. I don't, yet (but I know I will.) Curindor (if you don't remember, a randart cap rfire/life/dark/nexus) gets sold. I consider Mathom'ing Thengel, then decide to sell it, too, back in Lothlorien. (The armory here caps at 10k.) And then I decide I might as well get it over with: Maedhros and its bretheren get Mathomed. *SOB* 
