<h5 id="head-d9093a7e905cf2d7dcad611790e6849ccba4bcde">Land of Rhun 34 / good:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Smaller level, but larger than some. Precog shows Acid hounds coming toward me. I move northeast after them, losing a number of scrolls in the process. Now, in the distance, I see a group of Nexus hounds. At first I see only 4, then as I draw closer I see more and more (9 at least.) One of them breathes at me, and suddenly I'm on the far side of the map. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Precog shows a bunch of buildings. Two, halfway out of view on the map, look like pits or special rooms, and one of them is almost certainly an orc pit. A few more steps... yup, the one to the west is an orc pit. The other is a special room with a Dark elven lord in a tiny room at the center. A bunch of clear hounds are headed for me, and there's a Paladin I'm hoping to avoid. Piety now -12, but the orc pit should take care of that very nicely. I start on the hounds (cake), then notice the orcs are awake and headed straight for me out of the room. I switch to coward/running (from coward/brisk) and start in on it. I use a Mindwave or two, then hold off until I can get a clear LOS at most of the pit itself before I cast it again, depending on Barehand, which is doing well. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 At Pt 194, I am standing in the doorway of the pit. It's still about half full. Two Mindwaves later: Pt 346. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The Paladin finally catches up with me as I'm sorting through loot, and that wand of Teleport Away comes in handy. I go over to the other special room, and on the approach, I trip a Trap of Drop Everything. Gahhh. Well, at least it wasn't Scatter Everything! The Dark elven lord drops nothing interesting, and I keep going. I consider going on downstairs, but I've left a big chunk unexplored in the middle of the map, so I keep going. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Well, lookee there! A 5-headed hydra. It wakes and heads right for me. I kill it... and it doesn't leave a corpse . 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 To make up for this insult, a Mage drops a junkart (Large Crystal Ball-&gt;The Crystal Ball of The Witch-Kingo of Angmar), and a potion of DEX. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I see the Paladin trying to catch up with me, keep going, and run into those Nexus Hounds again. I'm promptly back across the map by the empty Orc Pit again. Feh- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-e1b984d73bde508149e4778cc752c48b2a24c3e6">Land of Rhun 35 / strangely lucky:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Smallish level. My pack's full again. Let's see here... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 What was that someone was saying about a very small vault with two traps in the bottom? I think that's what I'm seeing via Precog. As I'm sussing it out, a Dark elven priest comes up. He drops a potion of Charisma, which puts Slappy at 18/10. Ain't Slappy pretty, even though she's an it? 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 OK, the vault. The monster in the top half is a Giant fruit fly. Feh. I figure out where to enter the main vault, then where to enter the interior part. Fortunately, part of my loot is a staff of disarm, so the two unknown traps are easy work. Meanwhile, of course, the fruit fly is now 5 fruit flies. I get into that chamber, kill them easily (I'm still running, so +11 speed), and find a Feathers Cloak [1]. It IDs as a Feathers Cloak of Protection [1,+15], which is delightful, but I can't use it 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 There's a special room nearby that telepathy shows has a Mature white dragon inside. That's the first mature dragon I've seen outside of Angband wilderness. I stop by another room on the way to investigate a fountain, and find it holds Cure critical insanity. I'd be happier if it were Cure insanity, but... I destroy a Long Sword of Slay Demon, and stock up. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 On the way to the dragon, I kill a Ninja (first I've seen) who drops a Venomous Cleaver. I'm about to head in when a bunch of White Wolves appear, and I decide to clean them out. In the process, I enter another room and discover (much to my happiness) a Parchment - Numenorian for Beginners (I). Some of you might care less about this, but I use the "ure nimir" inscription all the time for my characters, as none of them (so far) have the Globe of Light spell, and I don't like wasting a slot on a Rod of Illumination. (Enlightenment... something else.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 OK, the mature white dragon is an easy kill. It drops..(ok, I'll give you the whole list, just this once ) rings of searching (cursed twice), spell, (pause for ID) strength(+2), plain jane Chain Mail and a cursed light crossbow and longbow. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I take a swing around the level and Precog for anything interesting. I see a yellow tilde and think at first it might be a junkart or a trap, but closer inspection shows it to be an Undead stargazer. Killed with no problem whatsoever, but just as a reminder to everyone: Look out for the water in swampy levels! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 A bit further: A Mystic. It never hits me (I dodge once), and it dies. It drops...drum roll, please... a wand of dig[1|1]. In the nearby surrounds, a big pack of light hounds, and a bigger pack of phase spiders. Feh. I cast Minor Displacement and create a jumpgate inside of a nearby room, then go north. The light hounds follow. (I'm not worried about them, I just don't want to have to waste time on them.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Precog from my new location to the north shows a Revenant, a Blue dragon bat (I've been killing a lot of dragon bats, btw), and two rooms with fountains in them. Minor Displacement again.... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 It fails; I think I picked a location too far away. I kill the dragon bat and walk to the room: Resist Cold in the fountain, a waste of my time. I head up to the next room... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 WHOA! A lot happens, very fast. I thought I'd had Precog casted here. Here's the message history: 
</p>
</li>

    </ul><pre>(pack overflows, I drop pot of rcold)
The Light hound breathes light.
It magically summons its kin.
The Phantom tries to blank your mind.
Your memories fade away.
The Spectre misses you. &lt;2x&gt;
The Phantom tries to blank your mind.
Your memories fade away.
The Ghost missed you. &lt;3x&gt;
</pre>Visible monster list shows a Phantom Beast, Ghost, Spectre, Dread, Phandom, and a Novice Possessor (soul) along with the light hound pack. What the heck happened? My detect invisible must have worn off... 
    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I cast Precog and then Mindwave. A previously unseen Experienced possessor (soul) collapses, along with the novice one and the Ghost. The Phantom Beast is immune. The Dread and Phantom aren't happy at all, and the Phantom blanks my mind again. My HP's fine (down 2 points). 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Oh - I'm standing in a room doorway, but they are after me three abreast since they don't care about doors. I Precog *again* (lest something else sneak up on me) and kill the Dread with Barehand, dodging repeatedly. The Spectre and Phantom are both trying to kill me, and my mind keeps getting blanked. I go after the Dread and kill it. I should have gone for the Phantom, since now it blasts my mind and I'm down to 211/252 Sanity and confused. A CCW helps with the confusion, and soon after I see, in the message recall, that I'm resisting at least some of these mind attacks, not to mention dodging like crazy. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 This time I target the Phantom. It dies... and then (literally) 10 seconds later, they are all dead. Of course, now the Light Hounds are piling in, but I'm not impressed. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The potions of Cure Critical Insanity potions I'm lugging around come in handy, and soon I'm back to normal. The loot is garbage, though, and I'm a bit disappointed about that. (Wand of ice storm 2|30, stave of fiery shield 3|10, essences, and a monstrous compendium.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I continue across the level, eventually finding a Young blue dragon who terrifies me before I kill it. Later, I'm moving through the corridor around a special room and run into a streamer of Araneas. They are filtering down into the corridor from a room just a square to the north; there's 13 in all according to the visible monsters list. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 One casts a fire bolt, another incants at me. I'm at 200/285. I try to cast Adrenaline Channeling, and fail. I just keep going. I'm down well below 200 hp (they're still casting at me) when I remember I have a potion of healing in my pack, and that heals me completely. Seconds later, they are all dead, and I'm at Pt 608 (Yes, this is pitiful, but it's better than -3000!) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I'm back approximately where I started by now (by that mini vault) and go down to- 
</p>
</li>

