<h5 id="head-1cfbd11156e83e40a623eedde062a83801fed1bb">Land of Rhun 36 / strangely lucky:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Smallish level. Good thing, my pack is (well, has been) full. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I move south (I landed in the northwest corner) and see a checkerboard room just north and adjacent to a checkerboard pit. In the area: Snagas, a bunch of Water trolls and Ologs, a Shardstorm (erk), Cloud giant, Wererat (must find it), a Cloud giant, etc. These seem to be in the pit and in a room nearby. Even further south is an Illusionist and an orc pack of at least 20, hanging out in the forest. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I move north, take out a couple of Ologs, and find another cluster of previously undetected Snagas even further north. I clean them out, then circle back south again. I'll fiddle with the loot later, as I've only 18 ID scrolls left. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Next stop: the checkerboard pit. The wererat is in there, and I get it (the screen was dark enough I didn't see the dark grey 'r' until I was hitting it). The Illusionist comes up behind me from the forest while I'm finishing off the wererat and Ologs, and regrets it. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Next: The room with the Water Trolls. Turns out there is also a Bodak and a Skeleton ettin in here. (Gee, my Piety's at 1077 after that! ) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 By now that nest of orcs way down to the south of me has filtered up and started attacking. Black orcs and Uruks. I mindwave a bunch of them, then I'm out of mana. Not to worry, killing them by hand just takes longer. I follow them down through the trees (there's a *huge* swath of loot behind me by now) and I see what I think are more Ologs and go after them. Unfortunately, the window that I'm now typing in is covering over the visible monsters list, andit's not til I'm halfway through them that I realize the 'O's are actually Merrows, including a Merrow mage, priest, and a Spectral Merrow. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 After the dust finally settles, I wander around wondering what to ID. I come across a Potion of CHA. Then a scroll of Prot Evil. I peer at my pack for a few moments and ditch my restore life level potions for the scroll. I don't bother ID'ing anything but bolts and jewelry, and find nothing interesting. (Anything else would just be AU.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Now in the southeast corner of the map, I see a big pack of acid hounds coming at me and don't feel like bothering. A gold firebird is there, too. I teleport and wind up (somewhat to my surprise) exactly where I wanted to be: the northeast corner, where I haven't been yet. Moving west, the firebird catches up with me, as do the hounds...and the firebird soon dies. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Despite my +11 speed, I see an 'e' coming at me surprisingly quickly: A Gauth. It dies without hurting me. The Acid hounds coming up behind me do a bit better. I keep going. I see the 2nd Sandworm I've seen in Rhun, and kill it. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I hate Blink dogs. They disrupt me a bit, but I get where I'm going: a mature blue dragon. (2nd mature dragon seen...) No good drops. Some good dodging between rooms etc and I get away from my pursuers. I explore a bit further, and then consider going down. Nah, I'll recall first -- almost no ID if I find something good next level down. WOR- 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


