Now I'm all saddled up and ready to finish the Land of Rhun...and maybe a few other things. Til next time! 
</p>
<h3 id="head-4fa117462e72b654ac06edbda7a6e5277e807f74">A Day in the Life #9: CL33 (The Land of Rhun DL36-38)</h3>
Recap: Barrow Downs, 1st God Quest, Orc Caves, Lothlorien spider quest, and Old Forest are done. Partway down Mirkwood. Most of the way down The Land of Rhun; currently adventuring in Rhun. Received the 2nd God Quest but haven't found the entrance yet. Have houses in Bree and Lothlorien; residing in Lothlorien. <p>
I need (amongst other things) rconf, rblind. I have a temporary source of SI, and I have remove fear, though not rfear. I would love to get a source of Reflection, as just about the only things that are hitting me now are spells. Granted, not all of them are bolts, but it would sure help. So would more Spirituality (for a better saving throw) but I'd rather get as much as possible via the God quests. 
</p>
<p>
My Piety has FINALLY gone into the black, but is still quite low. 
</p>
<p>
Oh yes, and I now have two Death Fates: DL1 and DL18. And it occurs to me that, since I've just received my 2nd God quest, I don't know what level I'll be entering in on. I don't THINK it will necessarily contain DL18 (seems more likely for god quest #3) but it's a tetch worrisome. 
</p>
<h4 id="head-b27ac782b294b685fcedb1a2352909aeb8b9ceb3">CL33, continued</h4>
<em>Lothlorien:</em> I'm all restocked, so away I go. <h5 id="head-449e042a96e43859b6afc648644200d13fa1f6c0">Land of Rhun 36 / very good:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 It's a little irritating when I get a decent feeling when I come back to a DL I've been on before. OK, once around the park, as it were. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Precog and 'M' show a foursquare special room and a smallish level, respectively. The special room is fairly close by. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The special room has a pile of novice rogues, an illusionist, a Clairvoyant, 12 Fire hounds, 5 Vibration hounds (well, I've already killed one), a White Wraith, pack o' snagas, some assorteds, a young bronze dragon, and Ulfast, Son of Ulfang. There's also a shrieker in there with the snagas and the casters. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Barehand and Mindwave make quick work of the hounds. The dragon and wraith are in the same little room right next to each other, and to my surprise, I manage to kill the dragon before the wraith ever wakes up. I didn't realize my stealth was quite that good; I guess being a card-holding Coward does help 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The Illusionist and Clairvoyant come out of the next room, first. I step in, Mindwave, and the snagas are dead. Then I kill the shroom. Then I start cursing because once more, I've forgotten to pray. RRrggghhh.... (I start praying.) Oh, and I've also picked up a new junkart, the infamous "something weird", aka Kelek's Practical Joke. I've only found it once before. (Junkarts never activate for the same thing twice, from game to game, unless by chance, but last time I found it it was worthless.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Umm.... where did the Ologs and the Mezzodaemon come from??? Answer: the botttom of the visible map, which the special room is almost on top of. Must remember to check those.... I recast Precog, and although I can only see a handful of monsters on the current visible map, the "visible monsters list" now suddenly has 56 monsters, including Shadowfax, steed of Gandalf, a Demonologist (eek!), a Revenant, Mindflayers, a Nexus Q, Black puddings, cave trolls, gargoyles, a pile of manes and war bears and a bunch of other stuff. Hrrmm... 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I use the 'L' commands to shift the visible map about a bit, and see another foursquare special room immediately south of the one I'm in... Well, that explains it. And now Draebor, the Imp pops up on my list as well. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The Mezzodaemon is on top of me immediately, straight through the walls. I *think* it came from the room to the south. It misses me four times. With barehand, I hit it twelve times (and miss once), and kill it, no damage to me. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Soon after, Ulfast goes down to only four blows. You know, I keep meaning to write something a little dramatic like "And with one last circle kick, Ulfast sinks to the floor".... but the message immediately preceeding opponent death is almost always something like "You demolish/cripple the {whatever it is}." or "You wound Ulfast, Son of Ulfang." 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Top special room is done, so I head to the southern one. The Demonologist and Draebor are what worry me the most. I cast Precog again (telepathy just expired) and see that the Demonologist is lurking just *outside* the room area, just outside of a Mindflayer. I decide to go for those first, though there's a whole slew of manes etc along the northern "racetrack" corridor around the room who are trying unsuccessfully to get my attention. I think that's Shadowfax to the east of them (haven't checked), but I won't worry about him now. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I kill the Mindflayer while the Demonologist helpfully summons an Erinyes right next to me. I cast Adrenaline Channeling and set explore to 'running'; my speed is now +20. The E goes first, then the Mindflayer. Then I turn my attention to the Demonologist. There's a bunch of Cave trolls trying (unsuccessfully) to hit my back, and I ignore them for now. I kill the Demonologist without it hitting me or summoning anything else, for which I am profoundly grateful. (Other chars of mind have had levelled Demonologist companions, so I know how dangerous they can be. The one I just punched into paste wasn't levelled, of course, but I was still concerned.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I pause to Recog again. Yup, that's Shadowfax alright, but I can't find Draebor anywhere. Is he invisible to Precog? Or maybe off the map, or... well, I'll find him. Meanwhile, a few Mindwaves wipes out war bears and a bunch of other critters, and here comes Shadowfax. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I've 26 mana left right now, and I debate casting Mindwave or renewing Adrenaline Channeling. I decide on the latter, as Shadowfax is pretty quick--three blows (missed) to my one. I fail to cast it, and Shadowfax misses me three more times. Now I don't have enough mana to try it again... just enough to cast one Mindwave, and I keep it in reserve just in case. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Urgh... a LOT of blows later (mostly missed on both sides, though I stun him a number of times), I see: "You feel yourself slow down." This means I was still hasted, earlier, from the first time I casted Adren. Channeling. Assorted observations: a) I wasted the mana trying to cast it again, blast it all! b) Shadowfax is now even more fast. c) Shadowfax is still at *******. I hang on to my mana, and switch to my crossbow and those lovely bolts of acid I found a while ago. Four bolts later, the nice horsey is at ****. I take it from there with Barehand. A LOT of blows later, Shadowfax goes to Horsey Heaven. (Actually, I really hate killing Shadowfax; he's one of my more favorites in the books.) After all that melee, I'm down to only 266/285. Not too shabby! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I've been leaning on the right arrow button, and the next thing I see is: 
</p>
</li>

    </ul><pre>You found a trap!
Gas sprouts out... you feel you transmute.
You identified the trap as Trap of Femininity.
</pre>Yay, Slappy is an Abbess again, not an... Abbitt? 
    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I clear out the southwest room and rest up to full HP and Mana, then go looking for Draebor. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Next room: The Mindflayer, black puddings and revenants. I take out the Revenant and start in on the Mindflayer when it blasts my sanity down to 139/236 (blinding and confusing me at the same time.) I quaff a CCW, see a Chthonian miss me and nearly have a heart attack (remember, I've played Z...) then laugh at myself. I activate my junkart of cure insanity, which brings me to 191/236, so its description lies! I manage to kill off the remainder of beasties in the room, then close the door and rest until *finally* I can see clearly again. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 The last (northeast) room holds a Nexus Q, a plain Q, a Death Sword, and a couple others. (Still no Draebor?) The Nexus Q disappears almost instantly, and I think my INT and WIS have been swapped. A single bolt each kills the other two. By now, my junkart of cure insanity has recharged, so I get sane again finally. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Draebor must have teleported off somewhere. I go looking for him. On the way, I find a room stuffed with Bats of Gorgoroth (blah) and Lemures. Once done with that, I find a Potion of WIS on the floor. A bit further, I find a fountain of cure insanity. I drain it despite having the junkart. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 A ways further, I run into another pack of ~ 20 Dark elven warlocks. I'm standing inside a room, they are streaming towards the open doorway. A couple of Mindwaves take out a few, then I cast Adren Channeling. That gets me to the doorway (through a number of them). That lets me have clear LOS on the rest (including a skeleton one.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Lots o' loot left over. I find a Parchment - Advanced Lessons of Numenorean. I can't remember if I've found that one or not - have to check my own posts but I read it anyway. Then I find an Orange Tome-&gt;Gamenlon's Summoning Manual. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Still can't find Draebor, then I run into a small pack of Multi-hued hounds. Casting Major Displacement takes me back to the double room area, and I catch sight of that Nexus Q again. I sneak up on it <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/idea.png" alt="(!)" height="15" width="15"> and kill it. I bypass a Fire Giant (too far away), move due north and... well, here's Draebor, off by himself in the trees. How odd. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I'm at full HP/mana, so cast Adren.Chann again. Then I pause to think, and cast Character Armor as well. (At this point, it gives me extra racid/fire/cold.) *Right* after I do this, Draebor summons 20 Gargolyles, a Tengu, and a Death quasit in one go. One Mindwave hurts them all (the quasit jumps away) but now I have almost no mana left. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Now the Death quasit chimes in and summons 6 Vrocks. I've got plenty of HP (281/295) left, but this is not going well. Did I mention I'm completely mobbed? I use the wand of noxious cloud -- it affects the Vrocks, the others resist. (I was curious) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I'm about to use controlled teleport to get out of the mob when I realize I'm standing right next to Draebor. I switch to berserker/running (the berserker part is probably dangerous, but I want the extra melee bonuses). I'm making fairly good headway when that little Tengu I was ignoring teleports me quite some ways away. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I find what I think is a safe place to rest up, near a building. A Spectre come through the wall at me; I kill it and it drops a potion of CON (finally!). Then a Master Vampire comes at me through the trees. Despite being confused, I kill it. It drops yet another junkart (a Black Gem-&gt;The Gem of Hate.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I move north, find yet another special room (room inside a racetrack) and Precog is now showing Lorgan, Chief of the Easterlings. What does that make, 4 uniques on this level?! In the distance I see a Vrock, which means I'm probably getting close to where I left Draebor. Drat. Killing Lorgan takes rather a while, and in the process I take a step north and the visible map changes to show 19 Energy hounds napping *just* north of the room I'm in, the Vrock, an Ogre priest and mage, etc. Lorgan drops some nice Sheaf arrows of Venom and a small sword of slay orc. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I see more ogres to the north and wander that way...then find myself pincered between a group of them an a Mature black dragon. I pay attention to the dragon, first, but there's a Cave ogre Mage in the mix, so I turn about and kill it first, then the dragon. In the process I take a step east, and now Lokkak, the Ogre Chieftain becomes visible through the trees. Make that five uniques! 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I maneuver a bit until I can see as many of the ogres as possible (now down to 12) plus Lokkak, and Mindwave. Repeatedly. Finally I'm down to 4 mana, many of the ogres are dead, and I barehand Lokkak...for a while...until he cries for the Gendarmes and gives up the ghost. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Turns out there's another Ogre mage, plus a lot more ogres hiding in the trees. They aren't so hard to get rid of, and I just start to rest when those Energy hounds decide to wake up. Drat. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Searching the loot turns up an Amulet of Regeneration and nothing else that interests me. (My ID scrolls are running low, so I don't ID any weapons or armor.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I move northeast, and see the Draebor/et al. group again. I kill the Death quasit, then Mindwave the Tengu (hurting others), barehand a few Vrocks to death, then try Mindwave one more time.... and lose it, it backfires. A big pile of loot is destroyed and I faint with the effort and become paralyzed. Draebor walks up and kicks me a few times, saying, "Don't try running away, because you're the one I'll find..." Now here is the interesting thing: I'm paralyzed. He misses me three times, and then, though still paralyzed, I dodge him. Apparently he doesn't like this, as he teleports me away, straight into the middle of a wolf pack. Here is direct copy of what happens next, I'll type it out as I think it's interesting (I'll save a dump, too): 
</p>
</li>

    </ul><pre>Draebor, the Imp teleports you away.
The Wolf wakes up. &lt;4x&gt;
The Wolf misses you.
The Wolf wakes up.
The Wolf misses you. &lt;2x&gt;
The Wolf wakes up.
The Wolf misses you. &lt;4x&gt;
The Wolf wakes up.
You dodge the Wolf attack!
The Wolf misses you. &lt;7x&gt;
You dodge the Wolf attack!
The Wolf misses you. &lt;78x&gt; (not a typo)
You dodge the Wolf attack!
The Wolf misses you. &lt;4x&gt;
You dodge the Wolf attack!
The Wolf misses you. &lt;13x&gt;
You dodge the Wolf attack!
The Wolf misses you.
You dodge the Wolf attack!
The Wolf misses you. &lt;17x&gt;
You can move again.
</pre>
    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 In other words, if those hadn't been wolves or something similarly low level, Slappy would most likely be pushing up daisies right now. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Once I can fight again, the remaining wolves are toast. I *really* want Draebor, but I'm standing within about 5 squares of a down-staircase, so I take the hint. <strong>very good</strong> feeling, indeed!!! 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-2a3191e0e719af31b3c7a003952ef7446ed2f592">Land of Rhun 37 / strangely lucky:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I'm planning on recalling right out, but I decide to roam just a tetch. I'm dodging Fire hounds (laziness) and some wolves, and read a WOR, when Precog catches a small vault in the distance. I read another WOR to cancel the first. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Nastiest inside the vault is an Elder Areana. I cast Adren-Chann, use Thrain to break through, kill a scruffy hobbit, then beat up (for a short while) on Elder Areana. It heals itself completely once, but soon succumbs. I've only lost 7 HP. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I kill off a Gorgimera, and that's the last of any fight inside the mini-vault. Across the top of the interior box, there's a bunch of 1x1 rooms (maybe 4-5?) that I have to dig through. Only keeper is a staff of healing. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 I roam a bit more, but this is a happily quiet level, so I WOR out with a sigh of relief. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-1df3a221d576f88a753eb802683fa2569bac1c8c-17">Lothlorien:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 I sell a few things, then start in on the junkarts. Kelek's practical joke sells; it activates for gain corruption. The Gem of Hate *IDs* for Death, and Gamenlon's Summoning Manual *IDs* for high stat loss. What a waste! The Sheaf arrows sell for a tidy 25460 AU - not bad for a store capped at 10k. (I'm always amused when it works out that way.) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Time to clear out the house again and move stockpiles of potions to Bree. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
(Intermission while restocking; the BM at Bree will persist in taunting me with randarts I can't use! But I do buy a Potion of DEX. More AC, yay!) 
</p>
<h5 id="head-1de6d795bbca90bacfa557d5d034f83ef511cf7c">Land of Rhun 37 / looks like any other level:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 Precog shows... a Lich (first I've seen), pack of Algroths headed by two Algroth priests, and a bunch of Halfling slingers, the latter two of which this character hasn't met before. The Lich dies easily, as do the others. (I had forgotten halfling slingers are evil; piety ka-ching! ) 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 Dread, Revenant....Druid, couple o' Mages, pack of Energy hounds, then a young MHD. Nothing exciting. A Necromancer drops a Potion of DEX. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<h5 id="head-9cd4d54bec357987052311cf46c47800a162182a">Land of Rhun 38 / superb:</h5>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 There's a pit of... what the heck is that? Looks like an Amphibian pit, first one I've ever seen. It's way at the edge of the screen, monsters I can see are frogs, salamanders, greater basilisk, etc. Weird. Closer to me, a clump of Mongbats (ick) and some wolves, and an odd looking room that is either just an odd room or a small vault. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 There's a yellow 'I' that's probably a Hummerhorn or some such in the trees, and I decide to kill it off before tackling  the vault, though I'm a bit leery of the Basilisks (turns out there's more than one.) I take a few steps... 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


<p>
<strong>'"Eeek!"</strong>' 
</p>
<p>
I'm not even sure exactly how it happened, but a Greater Basilisk got out of the pit. In a bare instant, she was blind, and then she was very, very dead. Somewhere down there in Rhun there's now a very nice little stone statue of Slappy. 
</p>
<p>
Sorry folks, I thought I'd at *least* get her to the bottom of Mirkwood and into Mordor before she bought the farm, but it just goes to show how the dumbest and unpredictable of things can kill you. 
</p>
<p>
I'm gonna go play with my Assassin for a while, til I get the bleahs out of my system. Thanks for all the feedback, it was a heck of a lot of fun! 
</p>
<h3 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h3>
<p>
